{"key":"post-13870301","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13870301</id>\n<content>You just keep getting deeper and deeper.&amp;nbsp; When it's 15% humidity outside during the winter, and you heat that air 50F to 90F degrees above the outdoor temperature, the humidity drops to 5% or less.&amp;nbsp; Indoor humidity should be in the 30% range for best comfort and health.&amp;nbsp; Everyone should run a humidifier, and if you're in a very cold climate like I am, run more than one.&amp;nbsp; A good rule of thumb is if your feet make static electricity from walking across the carpet, you need more moisture in the air.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As for humid air holding heat better than dry air, that's just basic first year physics.&amp;nbsp; Nobody is saying to turn a house into a steam bath.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13870312</next>\n<prev>13870279</prev>\n<first>13868151</first>\n<last>13872691</last>\n<when>1296321269</when>\n<utime>01/29/11 07:14 PM</utime>\n</post>"}